==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pectose
<hw>Pec"tose`</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦omac⟧s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pect</ets>ic + cellul<ets>ose</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An amorphous carbohydrate found in the vegetable
kingdom, esp. in unripe fruits. It is associated with cellulose, and is
converted into substances of the pectin group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pectosic</ent>⟦br⟧
